description: For sale: $794,900. Gorgeous renovated turn of the century Farmhouse style home. Enjoy the life by Lake Bde Maka (Lake Calhoun). This home boasts a gourmet kitchen w/ inset cabinetry, farm sink, integrated range and DW, Wolf and Subzero appliances and soapstone counters. Main floor includes a 3/4 bath with classic subway tile and Carrara marble. The second floor has 3 bedrooms, each with generous closets, and a full bath remodeled w/ vintage detailing. The 2nd floor deck is a wonderful spot to enjoy a glass of wine while watching the sunset over the lake. The finished 3rd floor bedroom, 3/4 bath, and sitting room could be your master retreat. New large 2.5 car garage built in 2019 with expanded concrete driveway pad. Enjoy a BBQ in the yard with the brand new landscaping and patio completed in 2019.

Easy access to 35W. This one won't last long!

One of the hottest areas in the Twin Cities!  Uptown is a thriving, vibrant, mixed-use neighborhood near the Mpls city lakes.  Walkscore of 94 (Walker's Paradise!) You can stay off road for hundreds on miles via this trail and connecting systems.

TWO underground side-by-side garage spaces. Amenities include a car-wash station, bike racks, dog run and herb garden. Solar panels on rooftops and LED zoned lights in the garage to reduce common area electric costs and keep HOA dues in check. Perched atop a Greenway entrance this green-inspired energy-efficient development is just blocks from lakes, restaurants, shops, bars & brew pubs. Stellar walk & bike scores! Well-run association. See 3D virtual tour.
